DECISION: APPROVE

SUMMARY: All acceptance criteria are met: Cargo.toml has correct crates.io metadata, the `publish-crates` CI job is properly gated on `build` and `release`, README and CONTRIBUTING.md are updated, and all 105 tests pass at 76.82% coverage. One minor inconsistency worth noting but not blocking.

**Note for awareness**: `src/bin/cpaste.rs` still exists in the repo. With the explicit `[[bin]] name = "copypaste"` entry present but `autobins` defaulting to `true`, Cargo still auto-discovers `src/bin/cpaste.rs` — confirmed by the validate log showing `copypaste::bin/cpaste tests::*` passing. This means `cargo install copypaste` will install both `copypaste` AND `cpaste` binaries. This is inconsistent with the issue's stated intent to replace cpaste, but doesn't break any of the five acceptance criteria. The fix would be to delete `src/bin/cpaste.rs` or add `autobins = false` in `[package]`. Given the tests depend on cpaste, a follow-up issue is the right venue.
